title: How to Watch ‘WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event’ Live Online

author: Rudie Obias
excerpt: After a 16-year hiatus, 'WWE Saturday Night's Main Event' returns to TV on Saturday, Dec. 14: Here's where to find and watch the WWE TV event online.
text: If you purchase an independently reviewed product or service through a link on our website, Variety may receive an affiliate commission. After a 16-year hiatus, “WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event” returns to TV, while former-pro wrestler and former-Governor of Minnesota Jesse Ventura also comes back to the broadcast table to announce the show. The pro wrestling event features five matchups on Saturday, Dec. 14. The main event features an Undisputed WWE Championship title bout with Cody Rhodes vs. Kevin Owens. “WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event” livestreams on Peacock and broadcasts live on NBC. Want to watch “Saturday Night’s Main Event” online? Here’s what you need to know. When Is ‘WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event’? Date, Time “Saturday Night’s Main Event” takes place at Nassau Veterans Memorial Coliseum in Uniondale, New York on Saturday, Dec. 14. The start time is 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT. How to Watch ‘WWE Saturday Main Event’ Online There are two ways to watch “Saturday Night’s Main Event” online. The first way is with a subscription for Peacock starting at $7.99/month, while the second way is on NBC with a subscription to DirecTV Stream (starting at $74.99/month), Fubo (starting at $44.99 for the first month, $79.99/month afterwards), Hulu + Live TV (starting at $82.99/month) or Sling Blue (starting at $22.50 for the first month, $45/month afterwards — channel availability and pricing vary depending on TV market). Although all four cable alternatives feature NBC, DirecTV Stream (5-day free trial) and Hulu + Live TV (3-day free trial) are the only two services that include a free trial, so you can watch “Saturday Night’s Main Event” online for free. ‘WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event’: Main Card Check out the “Saturday Night’s Main Event” match card below, and stream it on Peacock here. Match Card, 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT Cody Rhodes (champion) vs. Kevin Owens — Main Event, Undisputed WWE Championship Women’s United States Championship Tournament Finals Liv Morgan (champion) vs. Iyo Sky — Women’s World Championship Sami Zayn vs. Drew McIntyre Gunther (champion) vs. Finn Bálor vs. Damian Priest — World Heavyweight Championship Aside from “Saturday Night’s Main Event,” Peacock is the home to other sports leagues, including the NFL on NBC, Premiere League, PGA, NASCAR, IMSA, Big Ten Football and more. It’s also where you can find hit movies and TV shows, such as “Back to Black,” “Abigail,” “Oppenheimer,” “Lisa Frankenstein,” “Love Island USA,” “Bel-Air,” “The Traitors,” “The Killer,” “Mr. Throwback” and others. Watch all the action by livestreaming “WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event” online starting at 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT on Peacock, or airs on NBC via DirecTV Stream. Later in the week, tune into “WWE Raw” and “WWE Smackdown” after “Saturday Night’s Main Event.”

After a 16-year hiatus, “WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event” returns to TV, while former-pro wrestler and former-Governor of Minnesota Jesse Ventura also comes back to the broadcast table to announce the show. The pro wrestling event features five matchups on Saturday, Dec. 14.

The main event features an Undisputed WWE Championship title bout with Cody Rhodes vs. Kevin Owens. “WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event” livestreams on Peacock and broadcasts live on NBC.

Want to watch “Saturday Night’s Main Event” online? Here’s what you need to know.

When Is ‘WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event’? Date, Time

“Saturday Night’s Main Event” takes place at Nassau Veterans Memorial Coliseum in Uniondale, New York on Saturday, Dec. 14. The start time is 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT.

How to Watch ‘WWE Saturday Main Event’ Online

There are two ways to watch “Saturday Night’s Main Event” online. The first way is with a subscription for Peacock starting at $7.99/month, while the second way is on NBC with a subscription to DirecTV Stream (starting at $74.99/month), Fubo (starting at $44.99 for the first month, $79.99/month afterwards), Hulu + Live TV (starting at $82.99/month) or Sling Blue (starting at $22.50 for the first month, $45/month afterwards — channel availability and pricing vary depending on TV market).

Although all four cable alternatives feature NBC, DirecTV Stream (5-day free trial) and Hulu + Live TV (3-day free trial) are the only two services that include a free trial, so you can watch “Saturday Night’s Main Event” online for free.

‘WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event’: Main Card

Check out the “Saturday Night’s Main Event” match card below, and stream it on Peacock here.

Match Card, 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT

  • Cody Rhodes (champion) vs. Kevin Owens — Main Event, Undisputed WWE Championship
  • Women’s United States Championship Tournament Finals
  • Liv Morgan (champion) vs. Iyo Sky — Women’s World Championship
  • Sami Zayn vs. Drew McIntyre
  • Gunther (champion) vs. Finn Bálor vs. Damian Priest — World Heavyweight Championship

Aside from “Saturday Night’s Main Event,” Peacock is the home to other sports leagues, including the NFL on NBC, Premiere League, PGA, NASCAR, IMSA, Big Ten Football and more. It’s also where you can find hit movies and TV shows, such as “Back to Black,” “Abigail,” “Oppenheimer,” “Lisa Frankenstein,” “Love Island USA,” “Bel-Air,” “The Traitors,” “The Killer,” “Mr. Throwback” and others.

Watch all the action by livestreaming “WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event” online starting at 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT on Peacock, or airs on NBC via DirecTV Stream.

Later in the week, tune into “WWE Raw” and “WWE Smackdown” after “Saturday Night’s Main Event.”
